This paper is primarily focused on image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of novel weight initialization schemes and efficient computation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper applies its method to several existing CNN architectures, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
